reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:- Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, Mysticism, sections on union, apophatic mysticism, perennialism, Stace, Smart, and Zaehner, https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/win2023/entries/mysticism/: overlap: Already distinguishes Advaita identity with Brahman, theistic union or communion with God, Buddhist unconstructed experience, apophatic negation, and common-core versus constructivist interpretations.; difference: It sorts experiences and doctrines, not the handoff of loosened attention or ownership permissions in practice.; novelty impact: High reduction. The new model is close to a practice-language recoding of established mystical-experience typologies.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.md:- If: Changing the instruction at the handoff point should change later interpretation more than immediate perceptual content. Then: A practitioner given no-location language, witness language, or God-directed language after similar objectless calm should later describe different belonging or authorization, while reporting similar quiet or contentlessness. Weakens if: The initial phenomenology changes before doctrinal instruction, or the ownership language remains random after instruction. Test surface: Controlled meditation instruction study with post-session interview coding.
