reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.md:# Originality Audit: The Capacity Ledger of Gift and Effort
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.md:- Lindahl et al., The Varieties of Contemplative Experience, PLOS ONE, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239: overlap: Close to the failure-mode and safeguard claim. VCE identifies meditation challenges, interpretive frameworks, management strategies, teacher roles, practice factors, and sense-of-self effects.; difference: VCE does not propose a five-column capacity ledger or predict failures by gift-effort load distribution.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for the empirical-adjacent failure and support-structure components.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:# Originality Audit: Whose Doing Is This? Credit Distribution as a Practice Variable
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:Credit distribution is a separable practice variable. Traditions distribute the power behind transformation across practitioner-centered, source-centered, split-credit, activity-centered, and ground-centered patterns, and those patterns shape the felt quality of effort, failure meanings, safeguards, and practice dangers.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:- Credit distribution is separable from the capacity ledger, because two paths can require similar functions but credit their source differently.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:Structural observation: The SN 45.8 comparison is strong but slightly overstated. SN 45.8 makes effort operationally direct: the practitioner generates desire, endeavors, activates persistence, upholds, and exerts intent. Bhagavad Gita 3.27 denies egoic sole-doership by assigning actions to prakriti's gunas, but Bhagavad Gita 18.14 complicates this by listing five causes of action, including body, doer, senses, efforts, and divine factor. The better close-read is not that the Gita simply disowns effort, but that it embeds effort in a multi-causal anti-ego framework. This supports credit distribution, but weakens the clean split-credit classification.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:- Pargament et al., religious coping styles, accessible summary at https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC1630686/: overlap: Very close. The self-directing, deferring, and collaborative styles already formalize whether problem-solving responsibility rests in the person, God, or both.; difference: Credit distribution broadens from coping to contemplative and soteriological practice, adds activity-centered and ground-centered types, and predicts tradition-specific safeguards.; novelty impact: Very high reduction. The core variable is known under religious coping and control allocation.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:- Sri Vaishnava markata and marjara nyaya, overview at https://philosophy.institute/indian-philosophy/visistadvaita-path-liberation-bhakti-prapatti/: overlap: Close indigenous case. The monkey and kitten analogies formalize cooperation versus grace carrying entirely, with sectarian consequences.; difference: The candidate uses the case as one instance inside a broader typology and derives failure-mode predictions.; novelty impact: High reduction for the claim that traditions themselves recognize credit distribution as a live practice variable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:- Local Lumenary prior, The Forbidden Claimant Rubric and The Capacity Ledger of Gift and Effort, cited in the prompt: overlap: Near exact internal neighbor. Both ask where functions are held, who may claim them, and how gift and effort traditions distribute agency.; difference: The credit-distribution idea adds a named five-type typology and stresses separability from capacity location.; novelty impact: Very high internal reduction. These should be consolidated into one model.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:- If: Credit distribution should be separable from the capacity ledger. Then: Two traditions can require similar receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration functions while crediting the power behind those functions differently, and this difference predicts different safeguards. Weakens if: Credit distribution always collapses into support locus, or support-locus coding predicts safeguards and failures without a separate credit variable. Test surface: Paired coding of Jodo Shinshu and Christian grace traditions, Soto Zen and Dzogchen, Theravada and Gita karma-yoga, with independent raters.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:- If: Stage transitions should be high-risk points when credit distribution changes. Then: Manuals and teachers mark special danger when a practitioner moves from effortful preparation to recognition, surrender, no-gaining practice, or already-accomplished realization. Weakens if: Transitions do not show distinctive warnings, or reported difficulties are better predicted by retreat intensity, trauma, doctrine learning, or social pressure. Test surface: Stage-coded readings of Theravada, Sufi, Advaita, Dzogchen, Soto, and Pure Land training sequences.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:- Does naming credit distribution change practice guidance, or only translate familiar doctrine into comparative terms?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:- Merge this with The Forbidden Claimant Rubric and The Capacity Ledger unless a separability test proves credit distribution adds independent predictive value.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:# Originality Audit: The Forbidden Claimant Rubric
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:- The right audit unit is a two-part code: support locus plus forbidden claimant.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:- Religious locus of control and spiritual-health locus of control, overview at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Locus_of_control and related God-control literature: overlap: Close. Internal, external, God-empowered, and God-deferred control map directly onto support locus and agency attribution.; difference: Locus-of-control literature does not usually close-read practice manuals or distinguish support holder from forbidden claimant in contemplative training.; novelty impact: High reduction for support-locus originality, moderate preservation for the manual-coding rubric.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:- Sri Vaishnava markata and marjara nyaya, example overview at https://philosophy.institute/indian-philosophy/visistadvaita-path-liberation-bhakti-prapatti/: overlap: Close indigenous near-neighbor. The monkey and kitten analogies already encode different distributions of effort and grace.; difference: The rubric adds multiple support functions and forbidden claimant warnings beyond a two-model grace debate.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction, especially for the claim that traditions themselves divide over this variable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:- Local Lumenary prior, The Capacity Ledger of Gift and Effort, plus The Grain of Capacity, cited in the prompt: overlap: Near exact internal neighbor. The capacity ledger already asks where receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration are held across practitioner, vow, teacher, present act, and post-insight integration.; difference: The new rubric adds a sharper prohibited-owner column, but mostly develops the same architecture.; novelty impact: Very high internal reduction. This should be merged rather than published as independent.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:Unlike Pargament, religious locus-of-control work, self-power and other-power debates, monergism and synergism, and the local capacity ledger, this idea says that each required practice function should be coded twice: where the function is operationally supported and which claimant the tradition forbids from owning it.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:- Is support locus plus forbidden claimant already obvious as self-power, other-power, doership, gaining idea, pride, upaya, or ordinary lineage pedagogy?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:- Build the coding sheet with fields for function, stage, support locus, forbidden claimant, safeguard, and failure mode.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:# The Forbidden Claimant Rubric
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:- Near-neighbor search: Jack Engler, You Must Be Somebody Before You Can Be Nobody, https://inquiringmind.com/article/0501_1_engler-interview/; Bhikkhu Analayo, Skill in Means and Mindfulness, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12671-021-01795-2; Harvard Divinity Bulletin on Buddhist skillful means, https://bulletin.hds.harvard.edu/buddhist-studies-the-buddhist-way/. These sources cover ego strength, capacity-sensitive teaching, and pedagogical adaptation, but not a two-part code of support locus plus forbidden claimant across effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:- Build a coding sheet with five functions: receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration. For each cell, code support locus, forbidden claimant, stage, safeguard, and failure mode.
