reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.md:- The Capacity Ledger of Gift and Effort, observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort.md: overlap: Internal same-run neighbor. Both ideas use the five capacity variables and compare effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization.; difference: Capacity Ledger scores load placement. Grain adds directionality within each load and predicts resistance when a trained direction is repurposed.; novelty impact: Moderate to high internal reduction. Grain may be the more specific synthesis, but it depends on the same architecture.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.md:- If: Dual-trained practitioners should experience method-specific transfer resistance. Then: Vipassana-trained practitioners attempting Advaita self-inquiry should initially keep tracking change and non-ownership rather than resting in witness-recognition. Advaita-trained practitioners attempting vipassana should tend to seek a stable knower or background rather than evenly noting impermanence. Practitioners trained in non-attachment who enter devotional surrender should report affective restraint or suspicion of dependence. Weakens if: Practitioners report smooth switching with no directional pull, or reported resistance is fully explained by temperament, teacher instructions, language, or community identity. Test surface: Micro-phenomenological interviews with dual-trained practitioners, coded before doctrinal explanation is invited.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention.md:When experience is stripped down to seeing, hearing, sensing, and knowing, the live question is not only what remains, but who or what is allowed to receive the freed attention. One path leaves attention unowned: in the seen, only the seen, so no person can settle there. Another path gives attention back to the hidden seer: the seer cannot be seen because it is the Self that makes seeing possible. A third path offers attention upward: thought and creaturely desire are forgotten so the will can rest as a naked intent toward God. The same practical movement, loosening attention from objects and self-story, branches into different forms of custody: unowned attention, self-grounded attention, and surrendered attention. Traditions train the handoff of attention. They teach the practitioner not only what to notice, but where attention may belong after ordinary ownership has been weakened.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention.md:Close prior arguments usually compare self and no-self, witness-consciousness and pure awareness, or apophatic unknowing and emptiness. The sharper move here is to treat post-negation practice as a trained transfer of attentional ownership. That lets Christian apophatic prayer enter the comparison without being flattened into either witness metaphysics or Buddhist no-self, because love gives unclaimed attention a recipient. It also turns a doctrinal disagreement into a practice question: watch the exact moment when attention stops belonging to the usual self, then ask what the training permits next.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention.md:- If this model is right, then changing the instruction at the handoff point should alter later interpretation more than immediate perceptual content. If the initial experience itself changes before doctrinal framing enters, the model is weakened.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort.md:# The Capacity Ledger of Gift and Effort
